@startuml
title C4 Level 1 - System Context (NAPCORE Helpdesk)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #2B5FAB
  FontColor #1F2F4A
  BackgroundColor #F8FBFF
}
skinparam actor {
  BorderColor #2B5FAB
  FontColor #1F2F4A
  BackgroundColor #EAF2FF
}

actor "PTO\n(Public Transport Operator)" as PTO
actor "PTA\n(Public Transport Authority)" as PTA
actor "Developer" as DEV
actor "ITS System Integrator" as INTEGRATOR
actor "Ticketing Agent" as TICKET

rectangle "NAPCORE Helpdesk System\n(FAQ-first + RAG fallback)" as HELPDESK #DCE9FF
rectangle "Approved GitHub Repositories\n(NeTEx-CEN/NeTEx + allowlisted sources)" as GITHUB
rectangle "GraphDB Semantic Store\n(Ontology + alignments)" as GRAPHDB
rectangle "Controller Model Runtime\n(Intent, routing, SPARQL planning)" as CONTROLLER_LLM
rectangle "Narration Model Runtime\n(Grounded answer composition)" as NARRATION_LLM

PTO --> HELPDESK : Asks standards\nimplementation questions
PTA --> HELPDESK : Asks policy and\ncompliance-related questions
DEV --> HELPDESK : Asks technical\nintegration questions
INTEGRATOR --> HELPDESK : Asks interoperability\nand deployment questions
TICKET --> HELPDESK : Asks ticketing\nintegration questions

' Top layer: actors arranged horizontally
PTO -[hidden]right-> PTA
PTA -[hidden]right-> DEV
DEV -[hidden]right-> INTEGRATOR
INTEGRATOR -[hidden]right-> TICKET

' Bottom layer: external systems below helpdesk
HELPDESK -[hidden]down-> GITHUB
GITHUB -[hidden]right-> GRAPHDB
GRAPHDB -[hidden]right-> CONTROLLER_LLM
CONTROLLER_LLM -[hidden]right-> NARRATION_LLM

HELPDESK --> GITHUB : Retrieves approved\nsource documents and chunks
HELPDESK --> GRAPHDB : Queries concept graph\nfor semantic expansion
HELPDESK --> CONTROLLER_LLM : Runs controller prompts\nfor intent and route planning
HELPDESK --> NARRATION_LLM : Composes answer from\nevidence pack only

note bottom of HELPDESK
Knowledge boundary: approved GitHub repositories only.
If evidence is insufficient, system abstains.
end note

note right of NARRATION_LLM
Top layer: Users.
Bottom layer: Approved source repositories and model runtimes.
end note

@enduml
